			'A good visitation schedule for a 7-year-old gives the child predictable time with each parent without disrupting school, homework, activities, or friendships. If one parent has less overnight time, every other weekend plus a midweek dinner, activity attendance, school-event involvement, or extra holiday and summer time may work better than rare contact. When parents live close, a 60/40 or 70/30 schedule may preserve meaningful involvement while keeping one school-week base. The schedule should identify transportation, homework expectations, and activity responsibilities. Use the visitation calculator or parenting time calculator to understand overnights, but judge the plan by whether the child stays organized and connected.',
