			'Elementary school children often need schedules that protect school attendance, homework routines, friendships, activities, and consistent sleep. For many families, 2-2-5-5 and 5-2-2-5 are strong starting points because they create repeated school-night responsibilities while keeping both parents involved. Week-on/week-off can work better for older or highly organized elementary children when both homes handle school well. 60/40 may be more practical when one parent handles more transportation or parents live farther apart. The best schedule for an elementary school child is usually not the most complicated one. It is the plan parents can follow consistently while keeping the child prepared for school.',
