			'The best parenting plan for a 7-year-old includes more than a weekly custody rotation. It should define school transportation, homework routines, activity responsibilities, communication through school portals, parent-teacher contact, sick days, holidays, summer schedules, and how supplies move between homes. A parenting plan template can help parents write down details that are easy to overlook, such as who signs reading logs, where sports gear stays, and how birthday parties or school events are handled. The best plan is specific but not overly rigid. It should give parents enough structure to avoid conflict while still allowing reasonable flexibility for school projects, activities, and social events.',
