			'A custody schedule for a school-age child should include regular parenting time, exchange days, school pickup and drop-off rules, homework responsibilities, activity transportation, holidays, school breaks, summer changes, and communication expectations. It should also explain how backpacks, school folders, reading logs, devices, chargers, uniforms, sports gear, and project supplies move between homes. If the child participates in activities, the schedule should say how parents share calendars and who transports the child even when the activity falls on the other parent\'s day. A custody schedule template can cover the basic calendar, while a parenting plan template can capture the school-age rules that make the schedule actually work.',
