					<div>
						<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-muted">Original insight</p>
						<h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Forgotten Backpacks Cause More Problems Than Custody Percentages</h2>
					</div>
					<div class="grid gap-4 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary">
						<p>
							Many parents spend enormous effort debating 50/50 vs 60/40, but the schedule often succeeds or fails because of smaller school-age logistics: forgotten homework, missing sports equipment, unfinished school projects, unsigned reading assignments, and transportation gaps.
						</p>
						<p>
							A mathematically balanced plan can still feel chaotic if the child arrives without sneakers, a library book, or the folder needed for Friday. The child may then feel responsible for adult systems they are not mature enough to manage.
						</p>
						<p>
							For a 7-year-old, the best schedule is usually the one parents can run consistently for months. Use a <a href="/custody-schedule-template/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">custody schedule template</a> to define the weekly pattern, then add school logistics in a <a href="/parenting-plan-template/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">parenting plan template</a>.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-section">
			<div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
				<div class="soft-card rounded-[1.75rem] p-6">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">School Year vs Summer Schedules</h2>
					<p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary">Many families use one schedule during the school year and a different plan during summer. School-year schedules often prioritize homework, transportation, and activities. Summer can allow longer blocks, travel, camps, and more flexible weekday time.</p>
					<div class="mt-5 overflow-x-auto rounded-[1.25rem] border border-line bg-surface">
						<table class="min-w-[620px] w-full text-left text-sm">
							<thead class="bg-surface-elevated text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-muted">
								<tr><th class="px-3 py-3">Need</th><th class="px-3 py-3">School Year Needs</th><th class="px-3 py-3">Summer Needs</th></tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody class="divide-y divide-line text-secondary">
								{seasonRows.map(([need, school, summer]) => (
									<tr><td class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold text-primary">{need}</td><td class="px-3 py-3">{school}</td><td class="px-3 py-3">{summer}</td></tr>
								))}
							</tbody>
						</table>
					</div>
					<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary">Holiday breaks should be planned separately from the weekly rotation. Use a <a href="/holiday-custody-schedule/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">holiday custody schedule</a> or <a href="/holiday-visitation-schedule/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">holiday visitation schedule</a> to avoid confusion.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="soft-card rounded-[1.75rem] p-6">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Warning Signs the Schedule May Need Adjustment</h2>
					<ul class="mt-4 grid gap-2 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">
						<li>Homework is consistently missing or late.</li>
						<li>School performance or participation declines.</li>
						<li>The child is frequently late after exchanges.</li>
						<li>Activity conflicts happen every week.</li>
						<li>The child shows ongoing emotional stress around the schedule.</li>
						<li>Backpacks, books, uniforms, or equipment are often forgotten.</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">These signs do not automatically mean the schedule is wrong, but they suggest the family should review logistics, exchange timing, and communication.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-section">
			<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Typical Overnight Distribution</h2>
			<div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-[1.5rem] border border-line bg-surface shadow-[0_18px_44px_rgba(15,23,42,0.06)]">
				<table class="min-w-[760px] w-full text-left text-sm">
					<thead class="bg-surface-elevated text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted"><tr><th class="px-4 py-3">Schedule</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Parent A Overnights</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Parent B Overnights</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Common Label</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody class="divide-y divide-line text-secondary">
						{overnightRows.map(([schedule, parentA, parentB, label]) => (
							<tr><td class="px-4 py-4 font-semibold text-primary">{schedule}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{parentA}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{parentB}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{label}</td></tr>
						))}
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">Estimate exact totals with the <a href="/custody-percentage-calculator/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">custody percentage calculator</a> or <a href="/parenting-time-calculator/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">parenting time calculator</a>.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-section">
			<div class="premium-card rounded-[2rem] p-6 lg:p-8">
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Which Schedule Is Best for Your Family?</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
					{[
						['Choose 2-2-5-5 if...', ['Parents live nearby', 'Stable school nights matter', 'Both parents can manage homework', 'The child benefits from alternating weekends'], '/2-2-5-5-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose 5-2-2-5 if...', ['The child has activities', 'Longer blocks reduce confusion', 'Both homes can track school supplies', 'Equal time is realistic'], '/5-2-2-5-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose week-on/week-off if...', ['The child is organized', 'Fewer exchanges help', 'Both homes handle school fully', 'A week away is not too long'], '/week-on-week-off-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose 60/40 if...', ['Parents live farther apart', 'One home anchors school mornings', 'Equal time creates too much travel', 'The other parent still has meaningful time'], '/60-40-custody-schedule/'],
						['Choose every other weekend if...', ['Distance is substantial', 'One parent has limited availability', 'Fewer exchanges reduce conflict', 'Holidays and summer can add time'], '/every-other-weekend-custody-schedule/'],
					].map(([heading, items, href]) => (
						<a href={href} class="soft-card group rounded-[1.5rem] p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-accent/40">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-primary">{heading}</h3>
							<ul class="mt-3 grid gap-2 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">{items.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}</ul>
						</a>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-section">
			<div class="premium-card rounded-[2rem] p-6 lg:p-8">
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">What Parents of School-Age Children Often Underestimate</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary md:grid-cols-2">
					<p>School logistics can overwhelm an otherwise fair calendar. Backpacks, school portals, library books, reading logs, uniforms, and chargers all need a system.</p>
					<p>Transportation matters. A schedule that requires long drives before school or after practice may create stress even if the parenting time percentage looks balanced.</p>
					<p>Friendships matter more at this age. Birthday parties, playdates, and after-school events should not be ignored just because they fall on one parent\'s time.</p>
					<p>Communication between homes is the schedule\'s hidden infrastructure. If parents do not share school updates, the child may become responsible for adult-level logistics.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-section">
			<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Child Custody Schedules by Age</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-secondary">Age does not decide custody by itself, but it changes what the schedule needs to protect.</p>
			<div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-[1.5rem] border border-line bg-surface shadow-[0_18px_44px_rgba(15,23,42,0.06)]">
				<table class="min-w-[760px] w-full text-left text-sm">
					<thead class="bg-surface-elevated text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted"><tr><th class="px-4 py-3">Age</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Main Focus</th><th class="px-4 py-3">Recommended Reading</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody class="divide-y divide-line text-secondary">
						{childAgeRows.map(([age, focus, href, label]) => (
							<tr><td class="px-4 py-4 font-semibold text-primary">{age}</td><td class="px-4 py-4">{focus}</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><a href={href} class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">{label}</a></td></tr>
						))}
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="container-shell py-section">
			<div class="premium-card rounded-[2rem] p-6 lg:p-8">
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Helpful Custody Planning Tools</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3">
					{tools.map((tool) => (
						<a href={tool.href} class="soft-card group rounded-[1.5rem] p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-accent/40">
							<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-primary">{tool.title}</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">{tool.description}</p>
							<span class="mt-4 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 group-hover:text-primary">Open tool</span>
						</a>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="faq" class="container-shell py-10 lg:py-12">
			<div class="max-w-3xl">
				<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-muted">FAQ</p>
				<h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">Questions About Custody Schedules for 7-Year-Olds</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-6 grid gap-3">
				{faqItems.map((item) => (
					<details class="soft-card group rounded-[1.35rem] p-5">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-semibold text-primary">{item.question}</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-secondary">{item.answer}</p>
					</details>
				))}
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</BaseLayout>
